OL,3,CGovernment wrongly blocked M&S
OL,4,Cdemolition plan for London store, High
OL,5,CCourt told
OL,7,FThe inspector, David Nicholson, had
OL,8,Fsaid that the building was not "suited
OL,9,Fto meeting the needs for the site" and
OL,10,Fthat "meaningful refurbishment" was
OL,11,F"unlikely", meaning demolition was the
OL,12,Fonly option.
OL,14,FMr Nicholson also said that blocking
OL,15,Fthe plans would likely lead to the
OL,16,Fstore closing, which would cause
OL,17,F"terminal" harm to the "vitality and
OL,18,Fviability of the area" and meant the
OL,19,Fbenefits of the plans outweighed any
OL,20,Fharmful effects.
