OL,7,FHe continued: "It is abundantly
OL,8,Fapparently that the Secretary of State
OL,9,Fboth understood the inspector's
OL,10,Fconclusions and gave adequate reasons
OL,11,Ffor disagreeing with them."
OL,13,FBut in his written arguments, Russell
OL,14,FHarris KC, representing M&S, said that
OL,15,Fthis was a "legally faulty
OL,16,Fmisunderstanding" of national planning
OL,17,Fpolicy and that "no such presumption"
OL,18,Fin favour of reusing or refurbishing
OL,19,Fbuildings existed.
